The defendant Jacquelyn P. High was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess Drug Paraphernalia, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

CO: RMW, REP: Drost, CLERK: Liddle. ADA:  Megan E. Kelly   DF ATTY:  Shirlene Renee Perrin   DF:  Jacquelyn P. High appeared. Case called at 8:49 a.m. Court notes defendant was previously represented by Atty Brandt. Atty Brandt filed a Motion to Withdraw as Counsel. Court approved. DE is now represented by Atty Perrin. Atty Perrin states there is an agreement. ADA Kelly recites agreement.   Court reads charge and maximum penalty. DE pleads NC to Ct 1 in 15CM10. DE sworn. Crt reviews plea questionnaire and informs DE of rights. Crt finds DE freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights and makes plea. Attorney's stipulate to the facts. Crt accepts plea, finds factual basis and finds DE guilty of Ct 1 Possession of Drug Paraphernalia in 15CM10.  Sentencing arguments. 20 days to appeal. Crt orders:

- Court costs $243.00. 60 days to pay.
